WEBVTT

00:09.443 --> 00:12.380
PREVIOUSLY ON
"UNITED STATES OF TARA"...

00:12.413 --> 00:13.714
SO, ON THE SCALE
OF GAYNESS,

00:13.747 --> 00:15.383
I'M THINKING
ALEX WOULD BE A 10.

00:15.416 --> 00:17.251
WHAT DO YOU THINK I AM?

00:17.285 --> 00:18.286
LIKE, A 5?

00:18.319 --> 00:19.653
I AM NOT A 5.

00:19.687 --> 00:21.789
I WANT TO TALK
TO YOU SOMETIME

00:21.822 --> 00:23.757
MAYBE ABOUT...
MAYBE BUYING THIS PLACE.

00:23.791 --> 00:26.060
WE'RE SO EXCITED TO HAVE
OUR OWN LITTLE FAMILY,

00:26.094 --> 00:28.429
BUT CHARMAINE SAID SHE
CAN'T IMAGINE DOING IT
ANYWHERE BUT HERE.

00:28.462 --> 00:30.664
FOUND OUT TODAY
THAT THE BABY'S NOT NICK'S.

00:30.698 --> 00:32.166
IT'S NEIL'S.

00:32.200 --> 00:33.201
CHARMAINE'S PREGNANT
WITH YOUR BABY.

00:33.234 --> 00:34.535
WHAT?

00:34.568 --> 00:35.803
I DON'T KNOW.
WHAT DO YOU WANT ME TO DO?

00:35.836 --> 00:37.805
I WANT YOU TO GET HIM
TO SIGN SOMETHING

00:37.838 --> 00:40.274
SAYING HE'S NEVER GONNA
COME BACK AND TRY TO BE
A FATHER TO OUR KID.

00:40.308 --> 00:41.542
I'M NOT SIGNING
ANYTHING.

00:41.575 --> 00:43.544
YOU TOLD ME
TO GET AN ABORTION!

00:43.577 --> 00:45.646
I'M YOUR PRINCESS
VALHALLA HAWKWIND,

00:45.679 --> 00:47.481
AND YOUR WISH
IS MY ULTIMATE COMMAND.

00:47.515 --> 00:49.150
Would you ever
meet in person?

00:49.183 --> 00:50.451
SO, IF YOU EVER
GET TIRED

00:50.484 --> 00:52.220
OF PRETENDING TO BE
A PRINCESS ONLINE

00:52.253 --> 00:54.522
AND YOU WANT TO BE TREATED
LIKE ONE FOR REAL,

00:54.555 --> 00:56.557
I'D LOVE TO BE THE GUY
TO DO IT.

00:56.590 --> 00:58.359
DO YOU REMEMBER
SOMEONE NAMED MIMI?

00:58.392 --> 01:02.230
I HAVE THIS MEMORY OF YOU AND ME
AND THIS WOMAN NAMED MIMI.

01:02.263 --> 01:03.697
NOPE.

01:03.731 --> 01:05.433
[ BOTH BREATHING HEAVILY,
MOANING ]

01:05.466 --> 01:08.369
LAST NIGHT, I STOPPED
AT CAT FIVE'S FOR A BEER.

01:08.402 --> 01:11.105
YOU HAD A THING
WITH PAMMY?

01:11.139 --> 01:12.573
YEAH.

01:14.542 --> 01:16.177
I KNEW IT.

01:16.210 --> 01:19.113
OH, GOD, MAX.

01:28.856 --> 01:31.859
* OPEN UP THE SKY

01:31.892 --> 01:35.463
* THIS MESS IS GETTING HIGH

01:35.496 --> 01:40.368
* IT'S WINDY,
AND OUR FAMILY NEEDS A RIDE *

01:42.503 --> 01:47.275
* I KNOW WE'LL BE JUST FINE

01:47.308 --> 01:52.646
* WHEN WE LEARN
TO LOVE THE RIDE *

01:53.847 --> 01:58.752
* I KNOW WE'LL BE FINE

01:58.786 --> 02:05.759
* WHEN WE LEARN
TO LOVE THE RIDE *

02:05.793 --> 02:10.364
* I KNOW WE'LL BE JUST FINE

02:10.398 --> 02:14.735
* WHEN WE LEARN
TO LOVE THE RIDE *

02:17.371 --> 02:19.540
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]

02:24.545 --> 02:26.814
LET'S GO HOME, TARA.

02:26.847 --> 02:29.950
CHARMAINE, WE CAN'T.

02:29.983 --> 02:32.420
I DON'T EVEN KNOW
HOW TO GET THERE.

02:34.555 --> 02:36.257
HAPPY BY-SENNIAL, MIMI.

02:36.290 --> 02:38.526
AND TO YOU, TOO, GIRLS.

02:38.559 --> 02:40.328
GO ON, MY DEARS.

02:40.361 --> 02:43.631
IT'S A PARADE.
YOU'RE SUPPOSED TO HAVE FUN.

02:43.664 --> 02:45.533
DON'T TALK TO ANYONE.

02:45.566 --> 02:47.368
[ GASPS ]

03:06.954 --> 03:09.223
HEY, BUDDY.

03:09.257 --> 03:10.491
WHAT'S WRONG NOW?

03:10.524 --> 03:12.560
OH, I'M JUST
SLEEPING ON THE COUCH --

03:12.593 --> 03:13.827
BETTER FOR MY BACK.

03:13.861 --> 03:15.963
MM. COMPLETELY BELIEVABLE
EXPLANATION.

03:15.996 --> 03:18.732
AS YOU KNOW, I AM 8 YEARS OLD
AND VERY, VERY SLOW.

03:18.766 --> 03:21.302
[ SIGHS ]
IT'S COMPLICATED, MARSH.

03:21.335 --> 03:23.937
WELL, IF YOU GUYS GET DIVORCED,
I'M KEEPING THE HOUSE.

03:23.971 --> 03:26.974
I CAN'T CHANGE SCHOOLS.
SHAWNEE NORTH HAS GANGS.

03:27.007 --> 03:29.577
EVERYTHING'S FINE.

03:29.610 --> 03:32.246
WELL, I'M GOING TO
MAKE BREAKFAST.

03:32.280 --> 03:34.282
KNOW WHO WILL
ALWAYS BE TOGETHER?

03:34.315 --> 03:36.317
ME...AND WARM,
DELICIOUS STRUDEL.

03:36.350 --> 03:37.585
EVERYTHING'S FINE?

03:37.618 --> 03:39.387
YOU TELL ME.

03:39.420 --> 03:41.489
I DIDN'T SLEEP
WITH SOMEONE ELSE THIS WEEK.

03:41.522 --> 03:42.723
YEAH, NOT THIS WEEK.

03:42.756 --> 03:44.592
[ SIGHS ]

03:44.625 --> 03:46.927
I'M FUCKIN' WRECKED.

03:46.960 --> 03:49.297
I DON'T WANT PEOPLE
TROMPING THROUGH OUR LIFE.

03:49.330 --> 03:51.465
I WANT TO CALL OFF
THE OPEN HOUSE.

03:51.499 --> 03:53.601
THE SIGN IS UP. THEY PUT THE AD
IN THE PAPER. IT'S TIME.

03:53.634 --> 03:55.369
NICK AND CHARMAINE, THEN.
IT'LL BE DONE.

03:55.403 --> 03:56.670
JUST 'CAUSE
THEY'RE NEXT DOOR

03:56.704 --> 03:58.272
DOESN'T MEAN
YOU GOT TO SEE THEM.

03:58.306 --> 04:00.274
WE'RE HAVING THE OPEN HOUSE,
OKAY?

04:00.308 --> 04:02.876
WE JUST NEED PEOPLE
WHO WILL STAY OUT OF OUR LIVES.

04:02.910 --> 04:05.613
FIND SOME NICE INDIAN FAMILY,
JUST OFF THE BOAT --

04:05.646 --> 04:06.880
NO ENGLISH.

04:06.914 --> 04:08.516
MAYBE ONCE A YEAR,
I SAY,

04:08.549 --> 04:11.018
"GOOD MORNING, MR. GUPTA.
HAVE A HAPPY DIWALI."

04:11.051 --> 04:14.622
AND HE NODS,
AND WE GO BACK TO OUR...

04:14.655 --> 04:17.758
WHAT -- OUR LIFE?

04:17.791 --> 04:19.427
YEAH, IT'S COMING BACK.

04:19.460 --> 04:21.295
[ SCOFFS ]

04:23.397 --> 04:24.832
SUPERMAN SLEPT
WITH SOMEONE ELSE?

04:24.865 --> 04:26.734
YEAH, WE'VE DEALT WITH
A LOT OF SHIT, YOU KNOW?

04:26.767 --> 04:28.369
BUT I NEVER THOUGHT
HE WOULD DO THAT.

04:28.402 --> 04:30.438
REALLY? I DID.

04:30.471 --> 04:31.705
MM. TERRIFIC.

04:31.739 --> 04:33.507
I MEAN, SERIOUSLY,
HOW MANY PEOPLE

04:33.541 --> 04:36.076
HAVE YOUR ALTERS SLEPT WITH
SINCE YOU'VE BEEN MARRIED?

04:36.109 --> 04:38.712
[ SIGHS ]
I COUNTED ONCE.

04:38.746 --> 04:43.451
IN OUR LIFE, I THINK IT'S
SOMEWHERE BETWEEN 33 AND 35.

04:43.484 --> 04:47.388
I MEAN, GOD,
IT WAS BOUND TO HAPPEN.

04:47.421 --> 04:48.756
YEAH, BUT HE DIDN'T
JUST CHEAT ON ME.

04:48.789 --> 04:50.424
HE SLEPT WITH PAMMY,

04:50.458 --> 04:52.560
THE WORST PERSON
HE COULD HAVE POSSIBLY FUCKED.

04:52.593 --> 04:55.863
NO, THE WORST PERSON
HE COULD HAVE POSSIBLY
FUCKED IS PROBABLY ME.

04:57.831 --> 05:00.668
YOU SERIOUSLY
WON'T SELL US THAT HOUSE?

05:00.701 --> 05:02.403
NO! STOP ASKING ME
TO DO THAT!

05:02.436 --> 05:04.004
IS IT BECAUSE
YOU DON'T LOVE ME?

05:04.037 --> 05:06.440
NO! IT IS BECAUSE
I DO LOVE YOU.

05:06.474 --> 05:07.808
GOD,
I'VE FUCKING TOLD YOU.

05:07.841 --> 05:09.109
ALL THOSE WEIRD DREAMS
I HAVE

05:09.142 --> 05:11.579
ARE SOMEHOW
CONNECTED WITH THAT HOUSE.

05:11.612 --> 05:13.447
WHAT,
THE MIMI MOLESTY DREAMS?

05:13.481 --> 05:14.615
I NEVER SAID THAT!

05:14.648 --> 05:15.949
I JUST SAID
THAT WHEN I HAVE

05:15.983 --> 05:17.485
MY OBSESSIVE THOUGHTS
ABOUT THOSE GIRLS,

05:17.518 --> 05:20.488
IT'S ALWAYS THERE
AND NOT HERE.

05:20.521 --> 05:22.089
HAVE YOU EVER ASKED MOM?

05:22.122 --> 05:24.558
WHAT?
WHAT WOULD I ASK HER?

05:24.592 --> 05:27.094
LIKE..."HEY, MOM?

05:27.127 --> 05:29.096
DO YOU REMEMBER
SOMEONE NAMED MIMI?"

05:29.129 --> 05:32.966
OR -- I DON'T KNOW --
"MOM, WHO THE FUCK IS SHE?"

05:33.000 --> 05:34.568
I MEAN --
I MEAN, TRIP SAID

05:34.602 --> 05:37.037
YOU WERE ALREADY TRANSITIONING
BEFORE THE RAPE, SO --

05:37.070 --> 05:38.806
OH, GOD.
YOU KNOW WHAT?

05:38.839 --> 05:40.808
IF YOU USE THE WORD "RAPE"
OR "MOLESTY" ONE MORE TIME,

05:40.841 --> 05:42.810
I'M GONNA HIT YOU HARD
ON THE SIDE OF THE HEAD.

05:42.843 --> 05:44.712
GOD!

05:44.745 --> 05:47.681
WOULD HAVING A LITTLE
FUCKING GRACE KILL YOU?

05:47.715 --> 05:49.116
GRACE?

05:49.149 --> 05:50.784
YOU'RE TALKING TO ME
ABOUT GRACE?

05:50.818 --> 05:53.020
YOUR FUCKING MARRIAGE
IS ABOUT TO FALL APART!

05:53.053 --> 05:55.055
EVERYTHING --
YOUR MARRIAGE, YOUR KIDS!

05:55.088 --> 05:57.591
DON'T YOU THINK
IT'S WORTH ONE CALL TO MOM?

05:57.625 --> 05:59.593
I DON'T KNOW.

05:59.627 --> 06:01.895
JUST TO...ASK?

06:04.698 --> 06:05.666
Zach: WOW.

06:05.699 --> 06:07.134
YOU LOOK GREAT.

06:07.167 --> 06:09.470
YOU CERTAINLY KNOW
HOW TO DRESS FOR TENNIS.

06:09.503 --> 06:11.071
WHERE'S YOUR RACKET?

06:11.104 --> 06:13.874
OH, I HAVE TO RENT ONE.
I DON'T REALLY PLAY SPORTS.

06:13.907 --> 06:15.409
I'M, YOU KNOW...

06:15.443 --> 06:16.477
DELICATE?

06:16.510 --> 06:17.878
LAZY.
[ CHUCKLES ]

06:17.911 --> 06:19.547
BUT YOU OWN
THE ENSEMBLE?

06:19.580 --> 06:22.049
OH, I REQUIRE MANY GARMENTS
FOR MY MANY MOODS.

06:22.082 --> 06:23.751
THIS IS ACTUALLY
A COSTUME

06:23.784 --> 06:26.420
FROM A TENNIS-THEMED DANCE SHOW
AT MY SCHOOL.

06:26.454 --> 06:27.955
I PLAYED VENUS WILLIAMS,
BUT THEN I QUIT.

06:27.988 --> 06:29.590
HEY, WOULD YOU MIND

06:29.623 --> 06:31.759
IF I CALLED YOU "KATHERINE"
INSTEAD OF "KATE"?

06:31.792 --> 06:33.894
LIKE WHEN TOM CRUISE
TURNED "KATIE" INTO "KATE"?

06:33.927 --> 06:35.929
MADE HER START WEARING
THOSE ZAC POSEN SUNGLASSES?

06:35.963 --> 06:37.565
IS THAT A HINT?

06:37.598 --> 06:39.733
YOU WANT ME TO GET YOU
SOME ZAC POSEN SUNGLASSES?

06:39.767 --> 06:41.602
JUST TELL ME. WE CAN
STOP AT THE NORDSTROM
ON THE WAY TO TENNIS.

06:41.635 --> 06:42.936
NO!

06:42.970 --> 06:44.204
I'LL BUY YOU
FUCKING NORDSTROM'S.

06:44.237 --> 06:45.205
OH, MY GOD!

06:45.238 --> 06:46.974
OR THAT HOUSE.

06:47.007 --> 06:48.809
I'LL BUY THAT HOUSE AND MOVE IN
SO I CAN BE ON STANDBY

06:48.842 --> 06:50.744
TO MAKE SURE YOU HAVE
EVERY SINGLE THING YOU NEED.

06:50.778 --> 06:52.212
I GET IT --
YOU'RE RICH.

06:52.245 --> 06:55.115
WHOOP-DIDDILY-DEE.
ZACH CAN HAVE WHATEVER HE WANTS.

06:55.148 --> 06:57.818
THAT REMAINS
TO BE SEEN.

07:01.154 --> 07:02.656
OKAY, IT'S RINGING.

07:02.690 --> 07:04.825
I MEAN, SHE BETTER NOT
INSIST ON READING ME

07:04.858 --> 07:06.827
ONE OF THOSE FUCKING
CRACKED-OUT POEMS

07:06.860 --> 07:10.163
SHE WRITES FOR HER
"ACTIVE SENIOR" NEWSLETTER.

07:10.197 --> 07:11.799
HI, MOM!

07:11.832 --> 07:13.634
IT'S CHARMAINE.

07:15.268 --> 07:16.970
UM...

07:17.004 --> 07:20.207
YEAH, I'M NOT FEELING INCREDIBLY
HAIKU-ISH AT THE MOMENT,

07:20.240 --> 07:23.944
SO DO YOU THINK
YOU COULD READ IT TO ME LATER?

07:23.977 --> 07:25.679
HEY --

07:25.713 --> 07:26.714
MOM?

07:26.747 --> 07:28.015
MOM, I NEED TO TALK.

07:28.048 --> 07:31.218
YEAH, YEAH,
WE DEFINITELY SET A DATE.

07:31.251 --> 07:34.522
YEAH, NICK IS COMPLETELY
SUPPORTIVE ABOUT THE BABY.

07:34.555 --> 07:37.090
YEAH, HE IS --
VERY SUPPORTIVE.

07:37.124 --> 07:42.195
AS...SUPPORTIVE
AS...SOMEONE COULD BE,

07:42.229 --> 07:45.833
YOU KNOW,
WHO...ISN'T THE FATHER.

07:49.269 --> 07:51.505
UH, YEAH.

07:53.140 --> 07:55.509
UM...NEIL.

07:58.311 --> 08:00.080
YEAH, I KNOW.

08:01.549 --> 08:03.116
I KNOW!

08:03.150 --> 08:05.653
[ Voice breaking ]
THAT'S WHY I'M FREAKING OUT.

08:05.686 --> 08:07.621
I J--

08:07.655 --> 08:09.657
YEAH, I JUST --
I REAL--

08:09.690 --> 08:13.861
LOOK, I REALLY NEED YOU
TO COME HERE.

08:13.894 --> 08:16.096
I-I NEED --
I NEED MY MOMMY.

08:18.231 --> 08:20.200
OKAY. ALL RIGHT.

08:20.233 --> 08:21.602
GOOD.

08:21.635 --> 08:22.603
THANKS.

08:22.636 --> 08:24.037
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

08:24.071 --> 08:26.106
[ Normal voice ]
ALL RIGHT, SHE'S COMING.

08:26.139 --> 08:28.075
DO YOU DO THAT TO ME?

08:28.108 --> 08:29.910
JUST MAKE UP
WILDLY HEIGHTENED EMOTIONS

08:29.943 --> 08:32.012
JUST TO MANIPULATE ME
INTO BEING THERE FOR YOU?

08:32.045 --> 08:33.847
OF COURSE NOT.

08:33.881 --> 08:36.049
THAT'S JUST FOR MOM.

08:43.090 --> 08:45.626
GOD, I SHOULDN'T HAVE
LET YOU DRIVE.

08:45.659 --> 08:47.895
YOU'RE SWEATING
ALL OVER THE PLACE.

08:47.928 --> 08:48.896
NERVOUS?

08:48.929 --> 08:50.698
I'M NOT NERVOUS.

08:50.731 --> 08:52.933
I'VE BEEN TO THIS PARK
A HUNDRED TIMES ON SCHOOL TRIPS.

08:52.966 --> 08:55.002
YOU KNOW, IT'S THE SITE
OF THE ONLY WORLD WAR I MUSEUM

08:55.035 --> 08:57.037
IN THE WHOLE COUNTRY.

08:57.070 --> 08:59.673
YOU CAN'T TELL IT BY MY FACE,
BUT I'M ACTUALLY VERY EXCITED.

08:59.707 --> 09:02.342
LOOK, WE DON'T HAVE TO...
DO ANYTHING.

09:02.375 --> 09:05.078
WE JUST HAVE TO...
YOU KNOW, GET OUT OF THE CAR

09:05.112 --> 09:07.648
AND...SEE WHAT HAPPENS.

09:07.681 --> 09:10.217
THAT'S EASY
FOR YOU TO SAY.

09:10.250 --> 09:11.819
LOOK, BABY STEPS.

09:11.852 --> 09:14.888
IT'S JUST...
SHARING PARTS OF YOUR BODY

09:14.922 --> 09:16.757
WITH -- WITH A STRANGER.

09:16.790 --> 09:19.326
IT'S -- YOU KNOW,
IT'S NOT SCARY. I-IT'S HOT.

09:19.359 --> 09:21.261
IT'S SCARY.

09:21.294 --> 09:23.030
I MEAN,
HOW MANY MORE MERIT BADGES

09:23.063 --> 09:25.032
DO I HAVE TO EARN
UNTIL I'M GAY ENOUGH?

09:34.975 --> 09:36.209
Tara: HEY, MOM!

09:36.243 --> 09:37.945
WOW.
YOU LOOK GREAT.

09:37.978 --> 09:39.379
HOPE THE DRIVE
WASN'T TOO LONG.

09:39.412 --> 09:41.849
I THOUGHT YOU WERE
JUST A FEW MONTHS ALONG.

09:41.882 --> 09:44.051
WHY DO YOU ALREADY LOOK
SO PREGNANT?

09:44.084 --> 09:46.620
[ LAUGHS ]
I'M NOT EVEN SHOWING.

09:46.654 --> 09:49.089
YOU ARE IN YOUR FACE.

09:49.122 --> 09:50.691
Welcome.

09:50.724 --> 09:52.092
[ CHUCKLES ]

09:52.125 --> 09:53.360
[ SPEAKS MOCKINGLY ]

09:53.393 --> 09:54.828
[ CHUCKLES ]

09:54.862 --> 09:57.030
SO,
IT WORKS LIKE THIS --

09:57.064 --> 09:58.365
SOMEONE'S GONNA
COME UP TO YOU

09:58.398 --> 10:00.300
AND ASK YOU
WHAT YOU'RE INTO.

10:00.333 --> 10:03.837
AND IF YOU'RE INTO HIM,
THEN YOU GO OFF AND EXPLORE.

10:03.871 --> 10:07.174
WHAT, UH...
AM I INTO?

10:07.207 --> 10:09.176
I FEEL SO BAD
FOR BREEDERS.

10:09.209 --> 10:11.845
BEING GAY IS LIKE
LIVING IN A BUFFET.

10:11.879 --> 10:13.681
WHO DOESN'T LOVE
A BUFFET?

10:13.714 --> 10:16.884
ALL THAT MEAT UNDER THE HOT
LIGHTS AND THE SNEEZE GUARD.

10:18.886 --> 10:20.654
NICE DAY, HUH?

10:20.688 --> 10:22.022
LET'S TAKE A WALK.

10:22.055 --> 10:23.423
JOAQUIN.

10:23.456 --> 10:26.226
LET'S TAKE A WALK,
JOAQUIN.

10:29.229 --> 10:32.299
AND PEOPLE SAY
ROMANCE IS DEAD.

10:36.770 --> 10:38.205
WHERE ARE MY CRUDITES?

10:38.238 --> 10:41.975
IF YOU WANT CARROTS, JUST SAY
YOU WANT GODDAMN CARROTS.

10:42.009 --> 10:43.777
HEY.

10:43.811 --> 10:45.746
MY MOM'S HERE.
PLEASE ACT LIKE WE'RE HAPPY.

10:45.779 --> 10:47.915
I MEAN,
LOOK AT ALL THIS SPACE.

10:47.948 --> 10:49.216
HEY! BEV!

10:49.249 --> 10:51.251
TARA AND I ARE
REALLY HAPPY TO SEE YOU.

10:51.284 --> 10:52.953
WE'RE --
WE'RE HAPPY IN GENERAL.

10:52.986 --> 10:55.055
WHAT DO YOU THINK
OF A BIG CHANDELIER

10:55.088 --> 10:56.957
RIGHT IN THE MIDDLE
OF THIS ROOM?

10:56.990 --> 10:59.159
OH, YEAH -- LOTS OF GLASS.
BABIES LOVE GLASS.

10:59.192 --> 11:03.230
CARROTS? CELERY?

11:03.263 --> 11:05.766
DELICIOUS RANCH DIP?

11:05.799 --> 11:08.301
NEIL.

11:08.335 --> 11:10.237
NEIL?

11:10.270 --> 11:11.238
HELLO.

11:11.271 --> 11:13.006
COME ON, MOM.

11:13.040 --> 11:15.709
I'LL, UH, I'LL SHOW YOU
THE REST OF THE HOUSE.

11:20.080 --> 11:22.682
I'LL GO GET
SOME RADISHES, TOO.

11:30.223 --> 11:33.293
YOU DON'T HAVE TO
LOOK AWAY.

11:33.326 --> 11:35.062
NO. SORRY.

11:35.095 --> 11:39.867
YOUR, UM,
YOUR LUNCH LOOKS...

11:39.900 --> 11:41.201
I'M SURE IT'S GOOD.

11:41.234 --> 11:43.804
IT IS GOOD.

11:43.837 --> 11:45.739
[ SIGHS ]

11:53.113 --> 11:56.516
THIS -- THIS PLACE
IS REALLY WEIRD.

11:56.549 --> 11:58.018
SO, YOU WANT
TO COME BACK HERE

11:58.051 --> 11:59.419
SO I CAN INTRODUCE YOU
TO MY COCK?

11:59.452 --> 12:02.322
SORRY, FELLA.
HE'S WITH ME.

12:02.355 --> 12:04.024
I'M HIS FATHER.

12:04.057 --> 12:07.060
BOY, THIS IS AN EMBARRASSING
MIX-UP, HUH, SON?

12:07.094 --> 12:09.529
I'LL SAY...POP.

12:09.562 --> 12:13.233
WE SHOULD GET HOME
BEFORE MOM...SHOWS UP HERE, TOO.

12:13.266 --> 12:14.835
RIGHT.

12:14.868 --> 12:16.136
GOD.

12:17.938 --> 12:19.039
[ DOOR SLAMS ]

12:19.072 --> 12:20.373
DON'T SLAM THE DOOR,
TARA.

12:20.407 --> 12:23.110
SUCH UNNECESSARY NOISE.

12:23.143 --> 12:25.012
SIT DOWN, MOM.

12:25.045 --> 12:26.880
WELL, YOU'VE CERTAINLY
GOTTEN YOURSELF

12:26.914 --> 12:28.315
INTO A MESS, CHARMAINE.

12:28.348 --> 12:30.150
MOM, WHILE WE HAVE YOU HERE,
I WANTED TO ASK --

12:30.183 --> 12:31.384
CATTING AROUND
WITH ONE MAN

12:31.418 --> 12:32.820
WHILE WEARING
ANOTHER MAN'S RING.

12:32.853 --> 12:33.987
"CATTING"?
WHO SAYS "CATTING"?

12:34.021 --> 12:35.455
I KNOW --
EVERYBODY DOES IT.

12:35.488 --> 12:37.124
MOM, WHO'S MIMI?

12:37.157 --> 12:39.392
MIMI WHO?

12:39.426 --> 12:41.328
I THINK THERE WAS A MIMI AROUND
WHEN WE WERE KIDS --

12:41.361 --> 12:44.865
TARA, IF YOU COULD JUST
SHARE THE STAGE FOR ONE MINUTE,

12:44.898 --> 12:48.201
I CAME HERE TO DO DAMAGE CONTROL
ON YOUR SISTER'S LIFE

12:48.235 --> 12:49.302
AND PLAN A WEDDING.

12:49.336 --> 12:51.004
IT'S A FULL AFTERNOON.

12:51.038 --> 12:52.840
WELL, I'M ACTUALLY TRYING
TO DO DAMAGE CONTROL

12:52.873 --> 12:54.141
ON ALL OUR LIVES, MOM.

12:54.174 --> 12:56.910
IF YOU'D JUST...
ANSWER THE QUESTION.

12:56.944 --> 12:59.446
I'VE BEEN TRYING TO --

12:59.479 --> 13:03.083
I DON'T KNOW --
RECONSTRUCT MY CHILDHOOD,

13:03.116 --> 13:04.284
AND I --

13:04.317 --> 13:06.419
OH, NOT THAT AGAIN.

13:06.453 --> 13:07.487
OH, GOD.

13:07.520 --> 13:10.223
NO, IT'S NOT AGAIN, MOM.

13:10.257 --> 13:12.292
THIS IS SOMETHING
I'VE NEVER --

13:12.325 --> 13:15.395
[ Voice breaking ]
I'VE NEVER ASKED ANYONE.

13:15.428 --> 13:17.931
I KEEP REMEMBERING
A, UM...

13:17.965 --> 13:19.900
I KEEP REMEMBERING
A 4th OF JULY PARADE

13:19.933 --> 13:20.968
AND A WOMAN NAMED MIMI.

13:21.001 --> 13:22.302
NOW, WHO IS SHE?

13:22.335 --> 13:24.337
CHARMAINE, YOU KNOW
YOUR SISTER IS ILL,

13:24.371 --> 13:26.439
BUT YOU' THE ONE
WHO'S IN TROUBLE, MISS,

13:26.473 --> 13:28.308
AND YOU'RE JUST LETTING HER
GO ON AND ON

13:28.341 --> 13:30.944
ABOUT ALL THESE
STUPID LITTLE THINGS.

13:30.978 --> 13:33.246
GOD, MOM. WHY WON'T YOU
JUST ANSWER THE QUESTION?

13:33.280 --> 13:35.282
THAT'S WHY I'M HERE?

13:35.315 --> 13:38.118
TO PLAY SOME TWISTED GAME
OF "INSANE FAMILY JEOPARDY"?

13:38.151 --> 13:39.119
OH, GOD!

13:39.152 --> 13:40.988
THIS IS NOT A GAME, MOM.

13:41.021 --> 13:43.924
I'M AM FINALLY FIGURING OUT
WHERE I -- WHAT I COME FROM,

13:43.957 --> 13:45.392
AND THAT'S SANE!

13:45.425 --> 13:46.526
IT'S ALWAYS THE MOTHER,
ISN'T IT?

13:46.559 --> 13:48.161
[ LAUGHS ]

13:48.195 --> 13:51.264
I KNOW, I KNOW. I DIDN'T
READ TO YOU TWO ENOUGH.

13:51.298 --> 13:53.000
AND I DIDN'T
BREAST-FEED.

13:53.033 --> 13:55.335
NONE OF MY GIRLFRIENDS
WERE BREAST-FEEDING.

13:55.368 --> 13:58.005
NO ONE, OKAY?
SO SHOOT ME!

13:58.038 --> 14:00.640
I'M NOT BLAMING YOU, MOM.

14:00.673 --> 14:04.945
I'M JUST ASKING,
WHO IS MIMI?

14:04.978 --> 14:07.948
I DON'T KNOW, OKAY?
MAYBE A BABYSITTER.

14:07.981 --> 14:10.417
EVERYONE, STOP!
ALERT THE PRESS!

14:10.450 --> 14:13.086
BEVERLY CRAINE HIRED
A BABYSITTER ONCE OR TWICE.

14:13.120 --> 14:15.288
WHAT DOES IT ALL MEAN?

14:17.524 --> 14:19.292
OH, THANK YOU.

14:19.326 --> 14:21.061
[ HUMMING ]

14:21.094 --> 14:22.395
THANK YOU!
THAT'S VERY HELPFUL!

14:25.265 --> 14:27.968
I KEEP IMAGINING
A LITTLE GIRL

14:28.001 --> 14:32.239
WITH YOUR LONG,
LOVELY HAIR AND...

14:32.272 --> 14:36.009
NEIL'S FACE.

14:36.043 --> 14:37.978
AW, HONEY.

14:38.011 --> 14:40.647
YOU'RE SO PRETTY.

14:40.680 --> 14:44.384
BUT YOU'VE ALWAYS MADE DECISIONS
LIKE AN UGLY GIRL.

14:44.417 --> 14:47.620
I WANT TO TAKE YOU
TO SEE THE JOFFREY BALLET.

14:47.654 --> 14:51.091
IN CHICAGO?
YEAH, THAT'D BE FUN.

14:51.124 --> 14:53.126
BUT THIS IS
FOR TOMORROW NIGHT.

14:53.160 --> 14:55.428
WOULD YOU NEED TO CHECK IN
WITH YOUR PARENTS?

14:55.462 --> 14:57.164
ARE THEY GONNA MEET ME
AND WONDER

14:57.197 --> 14:58.598
WHAT SOME STRANGE OLD GUY'S
DOING IN YOUR LIFE?

14:58.631 --> 15:00.267
NO.

15:00.300 --> 15:01.969
MY MOM'S A STRANGE OLD GUY
SOMETIMES.

15:02.002 --> 15:03.070
LET'S GO.

15:03.103 --> 15:04.537
PACK A FEW THINGS.

15:04.571 --> 15:07.040
I'LL CALL THE PENINSULA
AND BOOK US A SUITE.

15:09.977 --> 15:11.411
I'M SORRY -- IT'S JUST...

15:11.444 --> 15:14.114
I'VE HAD A LOT OF SKEEVY GUYS
BOSSING ME AROUND,

15:14.147 --> 15:17.417
AND IT KIND OF MAKES THE FOOD
COME UP IN MY -- IN MY GULLET.

15:17.450 --> 15:19.486
I'M -- I'M SORRY.

15:19.519 --> 15:23.323
NO! I MEAN,
YOU'RE NOT A SKEEVY GUY.

15:29.762 --> 15:32.232
JESUS.
[ CHUCKLES ]

15:32.265 --> 15:33.233
WOW.

15:33.266 --> 15:35.268
UM, THIS --

15:35.302 --> 15:38.238
THIS REALLY IS A --
A TEENAGER'S ROOM.

15:38.271 --> 15:42.542
UH, THIS -- THIS IS NOT A ROOM
FOR AN ADULT TO BE IN.

15:42.575 --> 15:44.044
NO.

15:44.077 --> 15:46.413
NO, I PROMISE YOU,
THIS IS NOT ME ANYMORE.

15:46.446 --> 15:49.182
I WAS A LITTLE GIRL
WHEN I WANTED IT PINK,
AND I JUST HAVEN'T --

15:49.216 --> 15:52.652
UM...I-I MEANT ME.

15:52.685 --> 15:57.157
THIS IS NOT A ROOM FOR --
FORTO BE IN.

15:57.190 --> 15:59.326
I'M 27. I DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHAT I WAS THINKING.

15:59.359 --> 16:03.063
I-I-I HAVE TO
GET OUT OF HERE.

16:05.765 --> 16:07.400
LOOK, I BOUGHT YOU
THESE EARRINGS.

16:07.434 --> 16:09.369
YOU SHOULD
STILL HAVE THEM.

16:09.402 --> 16:10.537
AND -- AND --
AND KEEP THE TICKETS.

16:10.570 --> 16:12.039
NO!

16:12.072 --> 16:13.540
NO, YOU DON'T HAVE TO GO
TO THE BALLET.

16:13.573 --> 16:16.709
YOU CAN JUST...PUT THEM
ON YOUR BULLETIN BOARD.

16:19.112 --> 16:22.582
OH, MY GOD.
YOU HAVE A BULLETIN BOARD.

16:24.384 --> 16:27.320
[ HUMMING ]

16:45.238 --> 16:47.240
HEY.

16:47.274 --> 16:49.142
HEY.

16:49.176 --> 16:51.511
YOU OKAY?

16:51.544 --> 16:53.313
YEAH.

16:53.346 --> 16:55.048
JUST, YOU KNOW,
MY MOM.

16:55.082 --> 16:56.549
OH, YEAH, I SAW.

16:58.818 --> 17:00.520
YOU KNOW,
WHEN I WAS LITTLE,

17:00.553 --> 17:02.589
I GOT THIS, UH,
LEIF GARRETT ALBUM --

17:02.622 --> 17:04.524
"I WAS MADE FOR DANCING."

17:04.557 --> 17:06.193
[ LAUGHS ]

17:06.226 --> 17:07.794
BUT THERE MUST HAVE BEEN
A FUCK-UP AT THE FACTORY,

17:07.827 --> 17:11.531
BECAUSE WHEN I GOT IT HOME
AND PLAYED IT,

17:11.564 --> 17:13.300
IT WAS BLACK SABBATH.

17:13.333 --> 17:14.601
[ Laughing ] NICE!

17:14.634 --> 17:18.471
SO I EXCHANGED IT
AND GOT A NEW ONE.

17:20.107 --> 17:21.474
AND IT DIDN'T MATTER.

17:21.508 --> 17:24.211
EVERY TIME I LOOKED
AT LEIF'S HAPPY FACE,

17:24.244 --> 17:26.813
ALL I COULD HEAR
WAS "WAR PIGS."

17:26.846 --> 17:30.417
THAT'S WHAT IT'S LIKE...

17:30.450 --> 17:31.751
SEEING MY MOM.

17:34.787 --> 17:37.290
WELL, YOU KNOW, I --

17:37.324 --> 17:39.526
I CAN'T GIVE YOU
"I WAS MADE FOR DANCING."

17:39.559 --> 17:40.660
[ SIGHS ]

17:40.693 --> 17:43.096
BUT...
I CAN GIVE YOU THIS.

17:45.165 --> 17:46.766
WHAT IS IT?

17:46.799 --> 17:50.203
THE PAPERS THAT NICK'S FRIEND
SENT OVER FOR ME TO SIGN

17:50.237 --> 17:52.205
TO PROMISE, YOU KNOW,

17:52.239 --> 17:54.674
I'D STAY OUT
OF OUR DAUGHTER'S LIFE.

17:57.244 --> 18:02.782
I-I WANT YOU TO BE HAPPY,
CHARMAINE.

18:02.815 --> 18:07.220
I HOPE THIS HELPS.

18:07.254 --> 18:09.556
I SHOULD...
GET BACK INSIDE.

18:16.363 --> 18:19.699
UH, PROMISE ME ONE THING,
WOULD YOU?

18:19.732 --> 18:21.201
WHAT?

18:21.234 --> 18:23.470
YOU KNOW, IF SHE EVER
LOOKS IN THE MIRROR

18:23.503 --> 18:27.274
AND -- AND REALIZES
THAT SHE'S NOT NICK'S,

18:27.307 --> 18:30.510
UH, DON'T SAY BAD THINGS
ABOUT ME.

18:30.543 --> 18:34.547
YOU KNOW,
TELL HER I WAS A GOOD GUY.

18:34.581 --> 18:36.716
YOU KNOW, LIE.

18:40.187 --> 18:41.454
[ CHUCKLES ]

18:44.391 --> 18:46.159
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

18:46.193 --> 18:48.195
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOUR FUTURE PLANS ARE,

18:48.228 --> 18:49.696
BUT THAT BACK OFFICE
WOULD MAKE

18:49.729 --> 18:51.631
A GREAT EXTRA BEDROOM
FOR KIDS, MAYBE.

18:51.664 --> 18:53.233
HOW ARE THE SCHOOLS?
THEY'RE GREAT.

18:53.266 --> 18:55.468
BOTH OF MY KIDS
GO TO PUBLIC SCHOOL.

18:55.502 --> 18:58.505
MY DAUGHTER'S A SENIOR --
TOP OF THE CLASS.

18:58.538 --> 19:01.308
AND NEXT YEAR,
SHE'S OFF TO BROWN -- PRE-MED.

19:01.341 --> 19:03.176
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

19:03.210 --> 19:05.478
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

19:05.512 --> 19:08.181
I CAN JUST SEE THAT YOU TWO
REALLY LOVE EACH OTHER.

19:08.215 --> 19:10.450
AND THIS HOUSE WOULD
JUST MAKE A GREAT PLACE

19:10.483 --> 19:12.219
TO START A LIFE.

19:12.252 --> 19:14.721
[ As Alice ] HMM.
AN EVEN BETTER PLACE TO END ONE.

19:14.754 --> 19:15.722
[ LAUGHS NERVOUSLY ]

19:15.755 --> 19:17.390
THAT'S -- THAT'S ALICE.

19:17.424 --> 19:18.791
THAT'S TERRIFIC.
THAT'S FUNNY, ALICE.

19:18.825 --> 19:21.961
ALICE, THESE ARE SOME PEOPLE
WHO MIGHT --

19:21.994 --> 19:23.530
SORRY?

19:23.563 --> 19:25.665
OH, THIS IS A GREAT PLACE
TO DIE.

19:25.698 --> 19:27.300
DID ANYONE DISCLOSE TO YOU

19:27.334 --> 19:29.636
THAT THE PREVIOUS OWNER --
POOR DON --

19:29.669 --> 19:32.339
SPLATTERED HIS BRAINS
ALL OVER THE WALLS?

19:32.372 --> 19:35.408
YES, THIS WAS THE HOUSE
HE ALWAYS WANTED TO DIE IN,

19:35.442 --> 19:38.578
AND, BOY,
DID HE EVER DO IT.

19:38.611 --> 19:41.481
I WANT TO THANK ALL OF YOU
FOR COMING HERE TODAY TO MOURN.

19:41.514 --> 19:44.351
I KNOW THE FAMILY
WOULD APPRECIATE IT, TOO.

19:44.384 --> 19:46.553
DON WAS A BEAUTIFUL MAN.

19:46.586 --> 19:48.255
WE LOVED HIM SO.

19:48.288 --> 19:49.856
What the hell
is going on here?

19:49.889 --> 19:52.559
UH, THAT'S MY WIFE.
SHE'S ACTING A LITTLE GOOFY.

19:52.592 --> 19:55.428
GOOFY? THERE'S NOTHING GOOFY
ABOUT WHAT'S HAPPENING HERE.

19:55.462 --> 19:56.863
IT'S TRAGIC,
IS WHAT IT IS.

19:56.896 --> 19:58.765
SHAME ALL THE SUGARY
VANILLA SMELLS

19:58.798 --> 20:00.567
CAN'T TAKE AWAY
THE STINK OF THE DEATH.

20:00.600 --> 20:04.604
NO. NO,
THAT'S JUST BAKED IN.

20:04.637 --> 20:05.872
Bev: WELL. TARA.

20:05.905 --> 20:07.374
[ CHUCKLES ]

20:07.407 --> 20:10.577
THIS IS WONDERFUL --
REALLY WONDERFUL.

20:10.610 --> 20:13.580
JUST LOOK AT YOU.

20:13.613 --> 20:17.784
I GUESS YOU ALREADY KNOW
WHO MIMI PARMETER IS, DON'T YOU?

20:17.817 --> 20:19.752
WELL, GOOD FOR YOU.

20:19.786 --> 20:21.788
MAX, WOULD YOU PLEASE
GET HER OUT OF HERE?

20:21.821 --> 20:24.791
THESE PEOPLE
DON'T NEED TO SEE THIS.

20:24.824 --> 20:26.726
OH. I UNDERSTAND.

20:26.759 --> 20:28.261
MANNERS.

20:28.295 --> 20:30.797
THINGS BETTER LEFT
BEHIND CLOSED DOORS.

20:30.830 --> 20:32.999
HOWEVER, IF YOU CHECK
YOUR ETIQUETTE HANDBOOK,

20:33.032 --> 20:35.468
AS I FREQUENTLY DO,
I THINK YOU'LL FIND

20:35.502 --> 20:37.804
THAT MOST OF THE EXPERTS
AGREE --

20:37.837 --> 20:41.874
A MOTHER SHOULD NEVER LIE
TO HER OWN CHILDREN.

20:43.910 --> 20:46.045
MY DARLING, DO ME ONE FAVOR
WHEN YOU BECOME A PARENT.

20:46.078 --> 20:48.881
DO NOT FOLLOW
IN THIS ONE'S EASY SPIRITS.

20:48.915 --> 20:51.684
BECAUSE PEOPLE NEED TO KNOW
WHAT'S REAL

20:51.718 --> 20:54.621
AND WHAT'S A HORRIBLE
FUN-HOUSE MIRROR

20:54.654 --> 20:57.490
MEANT TO CONFUSE
AND CONFOUND.

20:57.524 --> 20:59.692
PEOPLE NEED TO KNOW.

20:59.726 --> 21:02.829
Bev: THAT WAS
VERY, VERY RUDE, TARA.

21:02.862 --> 21:04.797
Charmaine: STOP IT.
YOU KNOW THAT'S NOT TARA.

21:04.831 --> 21:06.366
I'M GOING HOME!

21:06.399 --> 21:09.402
I'M SICK
OF ALL THIS CRAZINESS.

21:12.071 --> 21:14.040
[ CAR DOORS CLOSE,
ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

21:14.073 --> 21:17.544
TELL NICK TO GIVE ME A CALL.
WE'LL TALK ABOUT THE HOUSE.

21:17.577 --> 21:19.045
WELL, MAX...

21:19.078 --> 21:20.847
SHALL WE SPLIT A COOKIE?

21:20.880 --> 21:22.281
[ CHUCKLES ]

21:27.954 --> 21:31.558
I-I ACTUALLY LIKE
THE WORLD WAR I MUSEUM.

21:31.591 --> 21:34.361
I...CAN NEVER
GO BACK THERE.

21:34.394 --> 21:37.664
I'VE RUINED WORLD WAR I
FOR MYSELF.

21:37.697 --> 21:39.666
I DON'T...

21:39.699 --> 21:41.968
I DON'T KNOW
HOW TO BE GAY.

21:42.001 --> 21:44.737
I-I USED TO THINK
THAT I WAS SOMETHING ELSE,

21:44.771 --> 21:48.541
LIKE THEY'D MAKE
A WHOLE NEW CATEGORY FOR ME.

21:48.575 --> 21:51.043
I LIKE GUYS, BUT...

21:51.077 --> 21:53.880
I LIKE OLD FILMS
JUST AS MUCH.

21:53.913 --> 21:56.416
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT TO CALL THAT.

21:56.449 --> 21:59.752
I THINK
IT'S STILL CALLED "GAY."

21:59.786 --> 22:05.425
WHEN I WAS YOUNG,
CRUISING'S WHAT WE ALL DID.

22:05.458 --> 22:09.462
I WAS SO FULL
OF SHAME AND ANGER.

22:09.496 --> 22:11.931
MY THERAPIST
CALLED IT "SHANGER."

22:11.964 --> 22:13.633
IS THAT WHAT
IT FEELS LIKE TO YOU?

22:13.666 --> 22:16.369
UM,
I'D REALLY RATHER NOT

22:16.403 --> 22:18.605
HAVE TO USE A WORD
CALLED "SHANGER."

22:20.540 --> 22:22.709
WOULDN'T YOU RATHER
FALL IN LOVE, MARSHALL?

22:22.742 --> 22:27.113
WOULDN'T YOU RATHER BE 16
AND IN LOVE?

22:27.146 --> 22:30.082
I MARCHED ON WASHINGTON AND
SHOPPED ON CHRISTOPHER STREET

22:30.116 --> 22:32.018
SO YOU'D HAVE THE CHOICE
TO DO THAT

22:32.051 --> 22:35.555
INSTEAD OF, YOU KNOW,
GOING TO THAT PARK

22:35.588 --> 22:38.591
AND GETTING OFF
ON SERVICING STRANGERS.

22:41.193 --> 22:45.097
I'M NOT GONNA TELL YOUR PARENTS
ABOUT THIS, ALL RIGHT?

22:45.131 --> 22:46.098
THANKS.

22:46.132 --> 22:47.967
BUT, UM...

22:48.000 --> 22:49.869
I ALSO THINK
THEY'D BE CREEPED OUT

22:49.902 --> 22:52.772
IF I TOLD THEM
YOU WERE THERE.

22:54.974 --> 22:57.410
SOUNDS LIKE A DEAL,
THEN.

23:00.913 --> 23:03.716
SO,
WHAT DO WE DO NOW?

23:03.750 --> 23:06.185
[ As Tara ]
WHAT CAN WE DO?

23:06.218 --> 23:09.922
CAN'T JUST SIT AROUND WAITING
FOR MOM NOT TO BE A LIAR.

23:09.956 --> 23:12.492
I MEAN, SHE'LL SAY, "HEY,
I'M TELLING THE TRUTH NOW,"

23:12.525 --> 23:16.596
AND SHE'LL STILL
BE LYING.

23:16.629 --> 23:18.164
YOU STILL
LOOK LIKE ALICE.

23:21.568 --> 23:23.603
BY THE WAY,
THANK HER FOR ME.

23:23.636 --> 23:25.171
SHE SCARED THOSE PEOPLE
AWAY.

23:25.204 --> 23:27.840
GUESS SHE WANTS ME
TO LIVE NEXT DOOR TO YOU GUYS.

23:27.874 --> 23:29.776
KEEP AN EYE ON YOU.

23:29.809 --> 23:32.512
KEEP AN EYE ON YOU.

23:32.545 --> 23:35.081
[ SIGHS ]

23:35.114 --> 23:39.519
MIMI PARMETER.

23:39.552 --> 23:43.055
WELL, AT LEAST
WE HAVE A LAST NAME.

23:43.089 --> 23:45.925
YOU KNOW WHAT?
I COULD FIND MIMI MYSELF.

23:45.958 --> 23:47.827
OKAY.

23:47.860 --> 23:50.897
HOW DO WE DO THAT?

23:50.930 --> 23:52.632
"WE"?

23:57.103 --> 24:00.507
I THINK SHE LIVED
IN A YELLOW HOUSE.

24:00.540 --> 24:03.009
OKAY, WELL,
THAT NARROWS IT DOWN.

24:03.042 --> 24:06.513
SO, YOU SHOULD GET
A MAP OF AMERICA,

24:06.546 --> 24:09.081
AND I'LL GET
A COLOR WHEEL.

24:09.115 --> 24:10.817
[ CHUCKLES ]

24:13.886 --> 24:15.722
[ SIGHS ]

24:19.892 --> 24:22.161
FANCY MEETING YOU HERE.

24:25.698 --> 24:28.067
HEY, DO YOU KNOW
ANYONE WHO'S HAPPY?

24:29.636 --> 24:31.103
NO.

24:31.137 --> 24:35.107
DO YOU KNOW ANYONE
WHO'S IN LOVE?

24:35.141 --> 24:36.576
MOM AND DAD, MAYBE?

24:36.609 --> 24:37.577
YEAH.

24:37.610 --> 24:40.079
AND THEY'RE MISERABLE.

24:40.112 --> 24:42.081
BUT THEY CAN'T SURVIVE
WITHOUT EACH OTHER,

24:42.114 --> 24:45.552
SO IT DOESN'T MAKE A DIFFERENCE
IF THEY'RE IN LOVE OR NOT.

24:48.287 --> 24:50.623
I'M GONNA HAVE
SOMETHING DIFFERENT.

24:50.657 --> 24:52.725
THEN GO FOR IT.

24:52.759 --> 24:54.861
BUT JUST SO YOU KNOW,

24:54.894 --> 24:57.229
EVERYBODY'S HOOKING UP
WITH EACH OTHER

24:57.263 --> 24:59.666
BECAUSE
THEY WANT TO TAKE THINGS.

24:59.699 --> 25:03.903
IT'S A CAR
OR...A TRAMPOLINE...

25:03.936 --> 25:07.607
OR...HAPPINESS.

25:07.640 --> 25:09.942
THEY'RE ALL THINGS.

25:09.976 --> 25:12.144
EVERYONE'S A TAKER.

25:12.178 --> 25:14.146
EVERYTHING'S A THING.

25:14.180 --> 25:17.016
WHEN DID YOU
BECOME AN EXPERT?

25:17.049 --> 25:20.086
I AM VERY WISE,
MARSHALL GAY HARDON.

25:20.119 --> 25:21.721
I'M FULL OF WISDOM.

25:21.754 --> 25:23.222
YOU WEARING EARRINGS
TO BED?

25:23.255 --> 25:26.826
IT'S WHAT I'M DOING NOW,
YES.

25:34.000 --> 25:35.635
MARSHALL'S DOWNSTAIRS,

25:35.668 --> 25:37.604
AND I JUST DON'T WANT
TO FREAK THE KIDS OUT ANYMORE.

25:37.637 --> 25:40.106
I WAS GONNA LET YOU
SLEEP UP HERE ANYWAY.

25:40.139 --> 25:41.974
CLIMB ABOARD.

25:50.983 --> 25:54.186
[ SIGHS ]

25:54.220 --> 25:56.322
BIG MISTAKE.

25:56.355 --> 25:59.759
PAMMY -- HUGE MISTAKE.

25:59.792 --> 26:01.027
I KNOW.

26:03.830 --> 26:05.765
I KNOW, HONEY.

26:07.366 --> 26:10.770
THANKS TO MY FUCKING
FUCKED-UP CHILDHOOD,

26:10.803 --> 26:12.972
ALL I DO ALL DAY
IS RUN AROUND BREAKING EGGS,

26:13.005 --> 26:16.676
SO I CAN'T REALLY BLAME PEOPLE
FOR TRYING TO MAKE OMELETS.

26:16.709 --> 26:18.344
[ SIGHS ]

26:18.377 --> 26:21.113
YOU CAN BLAME ME
A LITTLE.

26:21.147 --> 26:24.250
ALL RIGHT,
I'LL BLAME YOU A LITTLE.

26:26.252 --> 26:28.755
BUT I ALSO FORGIVE YOU.

26:28.788 --> 26:30.156
REALLY?

26:30.189 --> 26:31.357
YEAH.

26:31.390 --> 26:33.092
I MEAN,
NO ONE KNOWS BETTER THAN ME

26:33.125 --> 26:37.163
WHAT PAMMY HAS TO OFFER TO
